      "writtenOn": "2015-11-20T08:54:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, I realized you just tried to fix a bug, not introduce a new static variable. Let\u0027s forget about unordered_set\u003c\u003e for now then, and focus on the bug itself. The LazyInstance\u003c\u003e approach is still better in my opinion. Note that it will leak the object at library unload / program exit, which shouldn\u0027t be a concern for us. Otherwise, an alternative is to store the variable into the FrameBuffer instance, and pass a pointer to it in the EglWindowSurface constructor.",
      "parentUuid": "96865a95_8f63415b",
